                  q: 'How do you build LLM prompts cleanly and safely in Python?',
                  a: 'Use f-strings or string concatenation for parameterised prompts. Write a dedicated function that takes context and query as typed arguments and returns the prompt string. Always strip and normalise user input before interpolating it into prompts to reduce prompt injection risk. For production systems, consider Jinja2 templates for versioning and validation. Store prompt templates separately from code so they can be updated without a redeploy.',
