                  fix: 'Use pd.isna(x) for Pandas / mixed types, np.isnan(x) for NumPy floats (raises on None), or math.isnan(x) for pure Python floats. pd.isna() is the safest — it handles None, np.nan, pd.NaT, and pd.NA.',
